}]},{"name":"Elen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Helen  , now also used outside Wales. It is identical with the Welsh vocabulary word <i>elen</i> ‘nymph’, but this is unlikely to be the origin. It is found in Welsh texts from an early period as an equivalent of <i>Helen</i>, for example as the name of the mother of Constantine, finder of the True Cross."],"variants":[{"name":"Elin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Elen ."]}]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elen ferch Llywelyn was born about 1334, in Carrog, Merionethshire, Wales as the daughter of Llywelyn ap Cadwgon and Ellyw II ferch Maredudd. She had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Maredudd ap Thomas."},"et":{"about 1334–":"umbes 1334–Surnud","1318–Male":"1318–Surnud","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1322–Male":"1322–Surnud","1324–Male":"1324–Surnud","1326–Female":"1326–Surnud","1328–Female":"1328–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1334–Female":"1334–Surnud","1337–Male":"1337–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1293–Male":"1293–Surnud","ABT    1365":"umbes 1365","1330":"1330","1293":"1293","1337":"1337","1326":"1326","1324":"1324","1334":"1334","1322":"1322","1365":"1365","1320":"1320","about 1334":"umbes 1334","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Carrog, Merionethshire, Wales":"Carrog, Merionethshire, Wales","of,Is Coed,Cardiganshire,Wales":"Llys Y Coed, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1334–":"noin 1334–Kuollut","1318–Male":"1318–Kuollut","1320–Male":"1